   <head>On the Dutchess of Newcastle's Picture.</head>
  </front>
  <body>
   <lg xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" type="poem">
    <lg n="1" stanza_type="couplet">
     <l n="1" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">, , where you learn'd the Art</l>
     <l n="2" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">To paint the Goodness of the Heart</l>
     <l n="3" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">The flatt'ring Teint let others prize;</l>
     <l n="4" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">You call the Soul into the Eyes:</l>
     <l n="5" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">There we the various Virtues trace</l>
     <l n="6" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Of , and  Race.</l>
     <l n="7" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Thrice happy , to whose Arms</l>
     <l n="8" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Were destin'd never-fading Charms!</l>
    </lg>
   </lg>
  </body>
